com.microsoft.office.sfb.appsdk

Interface Conversation

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Observable

    public interface Conversation
extends Observable
    This interface represents a communication between one or more participants - created via a Skype for Business meeting or by ad hoc user action. It is managed via a set of services local to this endpoint. Services are fixed and cannot be added or removed. There is one service that manages each aspect of this endpoint's communication into the conversation: e.g. for chat messaging, a service for audio, a service for video etc. There is also a service that manages the history of previous events that occur during this conversation.

      • SUBJECT_PROPERTY_ID

        static final int SUBJECT_PROPERTY_ID
        Property ID for notifying that conversation subject has changed. Subscribers will be notified via the onPropertyChanged method on the Observable.OnPropertyChangedCallback interface with this property id. E.g. callback.onPropertyChanged(SUBJECT_PROPERTY_ID). Clients are expected to call the getSubject method to get the changed subject.
